Interface FlowGraph<V>

Type Parameters:
V - A node of the flow graph
All Superinterfaces:

public interface FlowGraph<V>
extends Graph<V,​FlowEdge<V>>
This interface represents a flow graph.

  • Method Details

    • addNode

      boolean addNode​(V node)
      Adds new node to flow graph if node does not already exist. If node is added returns true, else returns false.
      Parameters:
      node - Node to add
      Returns:
      true if the node was successfully added, false otherwise.

    • addEdge

      FlowEdge<V> addEdge​(V start, V dest, int capacity)
      Adds a new flow edge to a start and a destination node with initial flow of 0. If either start or destination node does not exist in graph, throws an NoSuchElementException. Returns the existing edge if edge already exists.
      Parameters:
      start - Start node
      dest - Destination node
      capacity - Capacity of the edge
      Returns:
      Newly created flow edge between start and destination node
      Throws:
      java.util.NoSuchElementException - if either start or destination node does not exist in graph

    • containsNode

      boolean containsNode​(V node)

      Parameters:

    • edgesFrom

      java.util.Collection<FlowEdge<V>> edgesFrom​(V node)
      Returns all edges from given node. If node is not given in the graph, throws a NoSuchElementException.
      Parameters:
      node - Node whose edges should be retrieved
      Returns:
      A Collection of all flow edges leaving the node
      Throws:
      java.util.NoSuchElementException - if node is not contained in graph

    • getEdge

      FlowEdge<V> getEdge​(V start, V end)
      Returns a flow edge going from start to end. Returns null if flow edge is not present or at least one parameter is null.
      Parameters:
      start - Start of this edge.
      end - End of this edge.
      Returns:
      A flow edge
